ath algebras: if $E$ and\n$F$ are countable, row-finite, no-exit graphs in which every path ends in a\nsink or a cycle and $K$ is a 2-proper and $*$-pythagorean field, then the\nLeavitt path algebras $L_K(E)$ and $L_K(F)$ are isomorphic as graded rings if\nany only if they are isomorphic as graded $*$-algebras.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 26 Apr 2016 19:05:13 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 15 Oct 2017 15:27:59 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 31 Oct 2018 14:02:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-08"}
