a imply an average logarithmic slope\n$\\langle\\gamma\\rangle=2.18\\pm0.03$ across the sample, with a scatter of 0.11\naround this value. The average slope and scatter agree with recent results\nobtained from stellar kinematics alone for a different sample of early-type\ngalaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 27 Apr 2016 01:44:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-05-25"}
