 changes its nature,\ni.e., attractive or repulsive, depending on the positions of the domain walls.\nIn the latter case, there emerges fractional Josephson vortices when two\ndegenerate ground states appear due to spontaneous charge-symmetry breaking,\nand the number of the Josephson vortices varies with the position of the domain\nwalls. Our predictions should be verified in multilayered Josephson junctions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 27 Apr 2016 15:10:26 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 25 Sep 2016 06:42:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-05"}
